ğŸ§  Simple One-Line Explanation

Crypto ATMs in India are community-listed machines where users can buy (and sometimes sell) cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin and Ethereum using cash or card, mostly found in major cities but without official regulatory licensing yet.

#Number of Crypto ATMs by Country (Approx. 2025)
ğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¸ 1. United States
~30,000+ crypto ATMs â€” by far the largest network in the world, making up about 80% of all machines globally.

ğŸ‡¨ğŸ‡¦ 2. Canada
~3,000+ crypto ATMs â€” second-most globally and widely spread across provinces like Ontario and British Columbia.

ğŸ‡¦ğŸ‡º 3. Australia
~1,100+ crypto ATMs â€” third highest count, grown rapidly in recent years.

ğŸ‡ªğŸ‡¸ 4. Spain
~300+ crypto ATMs â€” among the leading European countries in crypto ATM deployment.

ğŸ‡µğŸ‡± 5. Poland
~200+ crypto ATMs â€” one of the stronger European networks, recently surpassing some other regional leaders.

##What This Means

The United States dominates crypto ATM adoption by a wide margin.
Canada and Australia are the next biggest markets.
Spain and Poland represent leading countries in Europe with active adoption.
Most of these machines support buying (and in many cases selling) cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin (BTC), Ethereum (ETH), Litecoin (LTC), and others, depending on the ATM model.

#Countries that Accepted Cryptocurrency as Official Currency (Legal Tender)
âœ… 1. El Salvador (2021)
Cryptocurrency: Bitcoin (BTC)
Status: Legal tender (official currency)
Can be used to:
Pay taxes
Buy goods & services
Make salary payments
ğŸ‘‰ First country in the world to do this.

âœ… 2. Central African Republic (CAR) (2022)
