âš ï¸ Adoption is limited in practice due to infrastructure issues.

ğŸŒ Countries that Accepted Cryptocurrency as an Asset / Property / Investment

These countries do NOT use crypto as official currency, but legally recognize it as an asset for trading, holding, or investment.

ğŸŒ Major Examples:
India
Crypto is treated as a Virtual Digital Asset (VDA)
Legal to buy, sell, and hold
Taxed at 30% on profits
Not legal tender

United States
Crypto treated as property
Taxed under capital gains
Widely used for investment

Japan
Crypto recognized as legal property
Regulated exchanges
Strong consumer protection

Germany
Crypto treated as private money / asset
Tax-free if held for more than 1 year

United Kingdom
Crypto treated as digital asset
Regulated and taxable

Canada
Crypto recognized as a commodity
Legal for trading and payments (not legal tender)

Australia
Crypto treated as property
Capital gains tax applicable

